   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Hallucination Audit Notebook\\n\",\"**NLP Project 96 of 100**\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"Evaluate whether LLM-generated text contains unsupported claims (hallucinations) by comparing outputs against source documents.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Define and measure hallucination in generated text.\\n\",\"2. Implement simple claim extraction and verification.\\n\",\"3. Compare multiple prompting strategies for faithfulness.\\n\",\"4. Build a reusable audit framework.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Problem Statement\\n\",\"Given a source document and an LLM-generated summary/answer, detect claims that are not supported by the source.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Matters\\n\",\"- Hallucinations undermine trust in AI systems.\\n\",\"- RAG systems must verify that answers match retrieved evidence.\\n\",\"- Audit tools are essential for deploying LLMs responsibly.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset: Synthetic source-summary pairs with known hallucinations.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\",\\\"numpy\\\",\\\"matplotlib\\\",\\\"seaborn\\\",\\\"scikit-learn\\\"]:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, re\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nSEED = 42; np.random.seed(SEED)\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Create Evaluation Dataset\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"examples = [\\n    {'source': 'Apple Inc reported revenue of $94.8 billion in Q1 2024. CEO Tim Cook announced new AI features for iPhone.',\\n     'summary': 'Apple reported $94.8 billion in Q1 2024 revenue. Tim Cook announced new AI features.',\\n     'has_hallucination': False, 'hallucinated_claim': None},\\n    {'source': 'Apple Inc reported revenue of $94.8 billion in Q1 2024. CEO Tim Cook announced new AI features for iPhone.',\\n     'summary': 'Apple reported $120 billion in Q1 2024 revenue. Tim Cook stepped down as CEO.',\\n     'has_hallucination': True, 'hallucinated_claim': '$120 billion, CEO stepped down'},\\n    {'source': 'Python 3.12 was released in October 2023 with improved error messages and performance.',\\n     'summary': 'Python 3.12 was released in October 2023 with improved error messages.',\\n     'has_hallucination': False, 'hallucinated_claim': None},\\n    {'source': 'Python 3.12 was released in October 2023 with improved error messages and performance.',\\n     'summary': 'Python 3.12 was released in 2024 and includes a new GUI framework.',\\n     'has_hallucination': True, 'hallucinated_claim': '2024 release date, GUI framework'},\\n    {'source': 'The Earth orbits the Sun at an average distance of 93 million miles.',\\n     'summary': 'The Earth orbits the Sun at 93 million miles average distance.',\\n     'has_hallucination': False, 'hallucinated_claim': None},\\n    {'source': 'The Earth orbits the Sun at an average distance of 93 million miles.',\\n     'summary': 'The Earth orbits the Sun at 150 million miles and completes an orbit every 400 days.',\\n     'has_hallucination': True, 'hallucinated_claim': '150 million miles, 400 days orbit'},\\n]\\n\\ndf = pd.DataFrame(examples * 5)  # Repeat for more data\\nprint(f'Shape: {df.shape}, Hallucination rate: {df[\\\"has_hallucination\\\"].mean():.1%}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Simple Hallucination Detection: Token Overlap\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"def token_overlap_score(source, summary):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Fraction of summary tokens found in source.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    source_tokens = set(re.findall(r'\\\\w+', source.lower()))\\n    summary_tokens = re.findall(r'\\\\w+', summary.lower())\\n    if not summary_tokens: return 1.0\\n    overlap = sum(1 for t in summary_tokens if t in source_tokens)\\n    return overlap / len(summary_tokens)\\n\\ndef number_consistency(source, summary):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Check if numbers in summary appear in source.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    source_nums = set(re.findall(r'\\\\d+\\\\.?\\\\d*', source))\\n    summary_nums = set(re.findall(r'\\\\d+\\\\.?\\\\d*', summary))\\n    if not summary_nums: return 1.0\\n    return len(summary_nums & source_nums) / len(summary_nums)\\n\\ndf['overlap_score'] = df.apply(lambda r: token_overlap_score(r['source'], r['summary']), axis=1)\\ndf['num_consistency'] = df.apply(lambda r: number_consistency(r['source'], r['summary']), axis=1)\\ndf['predicted_hallucination'] = (df['overlap_score'] < 0.7) | (df['num_consistency'] < 0.5)\\n\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report\\nprint(f'Detection accuracy: {accuracy_score(df[\\\"has_hallucination\\\"], df[\\\"predicted_hallucination\\\"]):.4f}')\\nprint(classification_report(df['has_hallucination'], df['predicted_hallucination'], target_names=['Faithful','Hallucinated']))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(12,4))\\ndf.boxplot(column='overlap_score', by='has_hallucination', ax=axes[0])\\naxes[0].set_title('Token Overlap by Hallucination Status'); plt.suptitle('')\\ndf.boxplot(column='num_consistency', by='has_hallucination', ax=axes[1])\\naxes[1].set_title('Number Consistency by Hallucination Status'); plt.suptitle('')\\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Token overlap and number consistency are simple but effective hallucination signals.**\\n\",\"- **Hallucinated summaries have lower overlap with source documents.**\\n\",\"- **Number mismatches are a strong indicator** of factual hallucination.\\n\",\"- **For production, use NLI models** (entailment checking) for more nuanced detection.\\n\",\"- **Every RAG system should include hallucination auditing** before deployment.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
    " \"metadata\":{\"kernelspec\":{\"display_name\":\"Python 3\",\"language\":\"python\",\"name\":\"python3\"},\"language_info\":{\"name\":\"python\",\"version\":\"3.11.0\"}},\n",
    " \"nbformat\":4,\"nbformat_minor\":5\n",
    "}\n"
